@bc:shopsystem-bc-launcher
@scenario_hash:<hash>
Scenario: bc-container launch warns to stderr and proceeds when host .claude.json is absent
  Given the shopsystem-bc-launcher BC is installed
  And the host directory "$HOME/.claude" exists
  And the host file "$HOME/.claude/.claude.json" does not exist
  And no Docker container named "bc-shopsystem-messaging" is running
  When I run bc-container launch with BC name "shopsystem-messaging"
  Then the command exits zero
  And stderr contains the literal substring ".claude.json"
  And stderr contains the literal substring "not found"
  And the FakeDockerDriver records that a docker run was issued for "bc-shopsystem-messaging"
  And the FakeDockerDriver records that no exec_run was issued against "bc-shopsystem-messaging" copying any path ending in "/.claude.json" to "/home/vscode/.claude.json"
  And the FakeDockerDriver records that a tmux new-session exec_run was issued against "bc-shopsystem-messaging"
